<Base title="About" description="Murmmers Press publishes fiction with a healing element, brought to the world with the author's voice intact.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Fiction with a healing element</h1>

      <p>Murmmers Press makes books for the times being alive gets hard. Quiet stories that reflect you back to yourself, and voices that sit with you in the ache and ask nothing. That is what we mean by a healing element: not a cure, and not advice, but company for the carrying.</p>

      <h2>The work</h2>
      <p>Every book is edited to protect what makes it itself, never to smooth it into sameness. We correct and tighten what is on the page. We do not regenerate it. Where a book is best read in one sitting, we treat that as a gift to the reader, not a shortfall.</p>

      <h2>The author</h2>
      <p>The founding list is the work of Eric McLean, who directs the press. More voices will follow as the catalogue grows.</p>

      <h2>The spirit</h2>
      <p>We believe attention is a kind of care, and that a book held with attention can hold you back. That is the whole of it.</p>

      <p>If you are curious how the books are actually made, that is a story of its own. <a href="/how-we-work/">How we work</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
